Angular Mini Projects

This repository is a collection of small Angular projects designed to practice the Angular framework and implement various functionalities in unique applications.

Projects

This repository contains multiple small projects showcasing different features and API integrations.

Movie Search App

The Movie Search is a simple frontend application that allows users to search for movies using the OMDb API.

Key Features:

Search for movies by title

Display results with a poster, title, and release year

API calls to OMDb API to fetch data

Future Plans:

More specific search options (e.g., by year, director, or actor)

Detailed movie information display

Favorites list feature

Installation and Running

Clone the repository:

git clone https://github.com/Dmate889/Angular_mini_projects.git

Navigate to the project directory:

cd Angular_mini_projects

Install dependencies:

npm install

Start the development server:

ng serve

The application will be available at http://localhost:4200.

Technologies Used

Angular (vX.X.X)

TypeScript

SCSS / CSS

OMDb API (https://www.omdbapi.com/)
